Stage 3: Personalized Awareness and Omnichannel Engagement

Awareness in ABM is not about mass reach—it’s about meaningful reach. In 2025, successful ABM awareness strategies rely on omnichannel engagement tailored to each account.

High-performing channels include:

Content syndication with role-specific assets

Targeted email marketing campaigns

LinkedIn and B2B display advertising

Industry-specific thought leadership content

Webinars, whitepapers, and case studies

The goal is to position your brand as a trusted authority while addressing the specific challenges your target accounts are facing. Content should be educational, insight-driven, and aligned with the buyer’s stage in the journey.

Examples of awareness-stage content:

Industry trend reports for executives

Security or compliance guides for technical buyers

ROI calculators for finance stakeholders

Stage 4: Mid-Funnel Nurturing and Intent-Driven Education

As accounts engage with your content, the ABM funnel shifts into nurturing mode. This stage focuses on building trust, answering deeper questions, and demonstrating value.

In 2025, intent signals play a critical role here. By tracking content consumption, website behavior, and third-party intent data, marketers can:

Identify which accounts are moving closer to purchase

Trigger personalized follow-ups automatically

Deliver relevant content at the right moment

Effective mid-funnel tactics include:

Multi-touch email nurture sequences

Personalized landing pages

Account-specific webinars or demos

Retargeting campaigns aligned to intent

This stage is where marketing and sales alignment becomes essential. Sales teams should have visibility into engagement data so they can prioritize outreach to accounts showing high intent.

