Stage 5: Sales Enablement and Appointment Setting

A high-impact ABM funnel doesn’t stop at engagement—it drives real conversations. Appointment setting remains one of the most critical components of ABM success in 2025.

At this stage, marketing-qualified accounts are handed off to sales with:

Detailed engagement insights

Stakeholder-level interaction data

Recommended talking points and content

This enables sales teams to have highly relevant, value-driven conversations rather than generic outreach.

Key best practices include:

Sales playbooks aligned to ABM stages

Warm introductions based on intent data

Personalized messaging for each stakeholder

Seamless coordination between SDRs and marketing

Stage 6: Pipeline Acceleration and Account Expansion

Post-meeting engagement is often overlooked, but it’s essential for accelerating pipeline and driving expansion. ABM funnels continue to nurture accounts even after opportunities are created.

This includes:

Competitive differentiation content

Customer success stories and use cases

Cross-sell and upsell campaigns

Executive-level engagement programs

In 2025, ABM success is measured not just by deals closed, but by long-term account growth and retention.

Measuring ABM Funnel Success in 2025

